# Axiom AGENTS

This project follows Axiom conventions.

## App Actions

- Prefer reusable Action classes in `app/Actions` for business logic.
- Name actions by what they do, without requiring an `Action` suffix.
- Keep one focused public `handle()` method per action.
- Inject dependencies via constructor promoted properties.
- Generate new actions with `php artisan make:action "{name}" --no-interaction`.
- Wrap complex multi-model writes in `DB::transaction()` when appropriate.

## Architecture

- Prefer DTOs over associative arrays at application boundaries.
- Keep controllers thin and move business logic into actions.
- Reuse existing components and follow the current directory structure.

## PHP And Style

- Use `declare(strict_types=1);`.
- Prefer `final` classes by default.
- Prefer `readonly` objects when mutation is not required.
- Always use explicit property, parameter, and return types.
- Use constructor property promotion in `__construct()`.
- Use curly braces for all control structures.
- Avoid superfluous PHPDoc and inline comments.

## Quality And Tests

- Keep PHPStan, Rector, Pint, and related tooling strict.
- Prefer static-analysis-friendly code over clever shortcuts.
- Do not leave `dd`, `dump`, or `ray` in committed code.
- Add or update tests whenever behavior changes.

## Skills

- Use `.ai/skills/actions.md` for action patterns.
- Use `.ai/skills/dto.md` for DTO workflows.
- Use `.ai/skills/enum.md` for enum usage.
- Use `.ai/skills/crud.md` for CRUD structure.
- Use `.ai/skills/quality.md` for verification flow.
